      • fractionalDigits

        int fractionalDigits()
        Some economy plugins round off after a certain number of digits. This function returns the number of digits the plugin keeps or -1 if no rounding occurs.
        Returns:
        number of digits after the decimal point kept
        Since:
        1.0.0

      • has

        boolean has(java.lang.String playerName,
          double amount)
        Checks if the player account has the amount, a negative amount will always return false.
        Parameters:
        playerName - The name of the player to check
        amount - The amount of money to check if the player has. This should be a positive number, you can't obviously check if he has a negative.
        Returns:
        True if the player has the amount specified
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the amount was negative
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the playerName was null
        Since:
        1.0.0
